<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-24T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-24T03:00:00-05:00" n="1504" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1504">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Colling, Guy Thomas: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-24T16:00:00+08:00">June 24,
                                    1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 24—8:02 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1368. ReEmbtel 750, June 24.<note n="66" xml:id="d1504fn66">Same as
                                telegram No. 1360 from Nanking, <ref target="#pg_1178">p.
                                1178</ref>.</note> Delivered memo this morning to Aliens Affairs
                            Office accordance Deptel 727, June 22.<note n="67" xml:id="d1504fn67">Same as telegram No. 1259 to Shanghai, <ref target="#pg_1175">p.
                                    1175</ref>.</note> However, it was returned on grounds matter
                            outside jurisdiction this office and could only be handled by Shanghai
                            Aliens Affairs Office. Repeated Shanghai 758, Peiping 239.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>